WEBVTT

00:01.540 --> 00:04.420
♪♪

00:04.420 --> 00:06.540
Katie:
Flavor of Westport,

00:06.540 --> 00:08.170
where the hippest restaurants
in town

00:08.170 --> 00:10.290
offer samples
of their signature dishes.

00:10.290 --> 00:12.580
Wow. Quinoa pie,
kale on a stick.

00:12.580 --> 00:14.540
Things I would eat if I was
on the show "Survivor"

00:14.540 --> 00:17.120
and I already ate
every rat on the island.

00:17.120 --> 00:19.120
Greg, Katie, hi!
Greg: Hi.

00:19.120 --> 00:21.330
This is also a great place
to bump into the people

00:21.330 --> 00:23.170
I spend all week
trying to avoid.

00:23.170 --> 00:25.210
Have you guys heard about
the big shake-up at school?

00:25.210 --> 00:26.330
Did one of those
lonely moms

00:26.330 --> 00:27.620
finally do
10 minutes in the shed

00:27.620 --> 00:28.500
with that
sexy groundskeeper?

00:28.500 --> 00:29.830
No.

00:29.830 --> 00:30.960
The new chairs
I've been fighting for

00:30.960 --> 00:32.380
were approved.

00:32.380 --> 00:34.540
We now have lumbar support
for our children!

00:34.540 --> 00:36.580
Three things happen
when you become parents.

00:36.580 --> 00:37.790
You buy a minivan,

00:37.790 --> 00:39.620
you use the word "potty"
around adults,

00:39.620 --> 00:42.250
and every conversation
becomes about the kids.

00:42.250 --> 00:45.080
We have so much children's
medicine in the house,

00:45.080 --> 00:47.420
but I can never find those little
plastic measuring thingies.

00:47.420 --> 00:49.170
Where do they go?

00:49.170 --> 00:50.880
Probably hanging out
with all the missing socks.

00:50.880 --> 00:52.750
[ Laughter ]

00:52.750 --> 00:54.620
Missing socks!

00:54.620 --> 00:57.000
[ Laughs ]
This is so boring.

00:57.000 --> 00:58.960
[ Laughter continues ]

00:58.960 --> 01:03.330
Beets, fish oil,
pollen, and --

01:03.330 --> 01:05.290
oh, I'm forgetting one --
peanuts!

01:05.290 --> 01:07.330
Those are all of
Holden's allergies.

01:07.330 --> 01:08.540
Okay. Now I'll go.

01:08.540 --> 01:11.460
Hay weed, gluten,

01:11.460 --> 01:13.620
hypoallergenic foam...
Super boring.

01:14.500 --> 01:16.290
I can't believe you left me
with that couple.

01:16.290 --> 01:18.170
They took me through
the entire evolution

01:18.170 --> 01:19.920
of their son's pronunciation
of "blueberry."

01:19.920 --> 01:21.670
Don't recap that conversation
for me.

01:21.670 --> 01:23.380
I actually sat
in a hot Port-a-Potty

01:23.380 --> 01:25.120
for 20 minutes
to avoid it.

01:25.120 --> 01:26.580
We should go.

01:26.580 --> 01:27.670
I have to help Anna-Kat
write a five-minute story

01:27.670 --> 01:29.290
for the Kid Lit assembly
this weekend.

01:29.290 --> 01:31.380
I think she focuses better
after a string cheese.

01:31.380 --> 01:33.210
But not the yellow kind
or the white kind.

01:33.210 --> 01:34.710
The yellow-swirled-with-white
kind.

01:34.710 --> 01:35.750
Cheddarella.

01:35.750 --> 01:36.830
Remember that time
we gave her the store brand?

01:36.830 --> 01:38.290
Yikes-arella.

01:38.290 --> 01:39.750
Oh, my God.

01:39.750 --> 01:41.250
Now we're boring
ourselves.

01:41.250 --> 01:43.290
We have no life
outside of our kids.

01:43.290 --> 01:44.830
That's not true.

01:44.830 --> 01:46.460
Okay, the other day,
I was carpool lane --

01:46.460 --> 01:47.380
Uhp, that's the kids.

01:47.380 --> 01:48.710
Never mind.
We have no life.

01:48.710 --> 01:49.920
Hold that thought.

01:49.920 --> 01:51.880
My trans-fat sense
is tingling.

01:51.880 --> 01:54.380
I smell something...
fried.

01:55.920 --> 01:57.080
...they must be hanging out

01:57.080 --> 01:58.120
with the missing socks,
right?

01:58.120 --> 01:59.420
[ Laughter ]

01:59.420 --> 02:00.710
Hey, that's my line.

02:00.710 --> 02:04.540
♪♪

02:04.540 --> 02:07.330
Greg, at my funeral,
along with bagpipes,

02:07.330 --> 02:08.540
I want funnel cakes.

02:08.540 --> 02:10.500
I haven't tasted
a funnel cake this good

02:10.500 --> 02:11.790
since the Florida State Fair.
Mm.

02:11.790 --> 02:13.120
Are you from Florida?

02:13.120 --> 02:15.080
Yeah, born and raised.

02:15.080 --> 02:16.330
We just moved here
from Myrtle Grove.

02:16.330 --> 02:17.960
We used to play you guys
in football!

02:17.960 --> 02:18.960
What?!

02:18.960 --> 02:20.580
♪♪

02:20.580 --> 02:22.580
We must've partied
at the same tailgate

02:22.580 --> 02:23.960
at the Speedway.

02:23.960 --> 02:25.210
Do you know the secret
about the beer stand

02:25.210 --> 02:25.960
by the Quaker State sign?

02:25.960 --> 02:27.420
Flash 'em for a six pack?

02:27.420 --> 02:30.420
I never paid for a beer
in four years.

02:30.420 --> 02:31.540
[ Both laugh ]
Hold on.

02:31.540 --> 02:32.790
You're familiar
with John Stuart Mill?

02:32.790 --> 02:34.420
Of course! Greg: You
don't understand,

02:34.420 --> 02:36.210
you're the first person
to ever say that to me.

02:36.210 --> 02:37.750
No, no, I understand.

02:37.750 --> 02:39.330
We're two Mill-heads.
Okay.

02:39.330 --> 02:40.710
Your favorite essay collection
on three.

02:40.710 --> 02:43.000
One, two, three.

02:43.000 --> 02:45.460
"Two Letters on the Measure of Value"!
"Two Letters on the Measure of Value"!

02:45.460 --> 02:46.750
[ Both laugh ]

02:46.750 --> 02:48.330
So, have you gotten a feel
for the town?

02:48.330 --> 02:49.330
Oh, yeah.

02:49.330 --> 02:50.670
They should change
their motto to

02:50.670 --> 02:54.000
"Westport -- our foreheads
haven't moved since 1862."

02:54.000 --> 02:55.080
[ Both laugh ]
Yeah, yeah.

02:55.080 --> 02:56.830
"Westport --
our women own

02:56.830 --> 02:58.790
80% of the world's
tennis skirts."

02:58.790 --> 03:00.170
[ Both laugh ]

03:00.170 --> 03:01.170
Hey, babe,
we better get going.

03:01.170 --> 03:02.460
Where you off to?

03:02.460 --> 03:04.580
Oh, we have tickets
for a cruise around Sagatuck.

03:04.580 --> 03:06.380
But, hey,
we should get together sometime.

03:06.380 --> 03:07.080
Here is my card.

03:07.080 --> 03:08.210
Thanks.

03:08.210 --> 03:09.750
See you, guys.
See you later.

03:09.750 --> 03:10.540
Katie: Bye!
Bye!

03:11.500 --> 03:12.540
I loved her!

03:12.540 --> 03:13.830
I loved him!

03:13.830 --> 03:14.960
I can't believe
we finally found a couple

03:14.960 --> 03:16.460
that we both like!

03:16.460 --> 03:18.040
Don't get your hopes up
about Courtney and Zach.

03:18.040 --> 03:19.540
I saw them move in.

03:19.540 --> 03:20.710
They don't have kids.

03:20.710 --> 03:22.210
Damn.

03:22.210 --> 03:23.880
Why?
What's the big deal?

03:23.880 --> 03:26.620
Couples without kids
hate couples with kids.

03:26.620 --> 03:28.830
Then she said
"boo-bewwy."

03:28.830 --> 03:30.330
Wait. No.

03:30.330 --> 03:32.540
First, three months,
he said "bwoo-bewwy."

03:32.540 --> 03:34.380
[ Laughter ]

03:34.380 --> 03:37.620
'Cause couples with kids
are so b-o-o-oring.

03:37.620 --> 03:38.710
♪♪

03:38.710 --> 03:40.040
Mmm!

03:40.040 --> 03:41.170
Looks good.

03:41.170 --> 03:42.250
♪♪

03:47.540 --> 03:51.000
♪♪

03:51.000 --> 03:51.710
I was thinking.

03:51.710 --> 03:53.120
Is it so inconceivable

03:53.120 --> 03:54.460
we could be friends
with Courtney and Zach?

03:54.460 --> 03:56.120
These people have
exciting lives.

03:56.120 --> 03:57.710
They don't want to hang out
with parents.

03:57.710 --> 03:58.540
We've got baggage.

04:00.170 --> 04:02.620
Here comes
the middle bag now.

04:02.620 --> 04:05.250
Mom, a word about
the quality of our lunches.

04:05.250 --> 04:07.250
Are they not up to your standards?
No.

04:07.250 --> 04:08.790
Would it kill you
to dry the lettuce

04:08.790 --> 04:09.830
before
you make the sandwich?

04:09.830 --> 04:11.290
I don't know.

04:11.290 --> 04:12.710
Would it kill you
if I put you in burlap sack

04:12.710 --> 04:14.170
with a couple of bricks
and threw you off a bridge?

04:15.920 --> 04:17.040
I think you should go.

04:19.040 --> 04:20.460
What if we just
don't mention the kids?

04:20.460 --> 04:21.620
Interesting.

04:21.620 --> 04:23.710
So you want to lie?
Not lie.

04:23.710 --> 04:25.790
Just hide the truth until they're
deeper in the relationship.

04:25.790 --> 04:27.290
You know, like you did
when we were dating.

04:27.290 --> 04:29.210
You thought
I liked foreign films.

04:29.210 --> 04:30.670
Ooh, "Chocolat"!

04:30.670 --> 04:31.790
That was in English.

04:31.790 --> 04:32.670
It felt foreign.

04:32.670 --> 04:33.920
But you're right.

04:33.920 --> 04:35.040
We just won't
mention the kids.

04:36.080 --> 04:37.620
Let me do the talking.
Why?

04:37.620 --> 04:39.330
Because your voice gets all high
when you're nervous.

04:39.330 --> 04:40.540
It does?

04:40.540 --> 04:42.040
Is that why they're
always calling me "ma'am"

04:42.040 --> 04:43.330
when I order
at drive-throughs?

04:43.330 --> 04:44.750
Who the hell gets nervous
at a drive-through?

04:44.750 --> 04:45.750
It's a lot of pressure.

04:45.750 --> 04:47.000
People are waiting.

04:47.000 --> 04:48.420
They can't always
hear you.

04:48.420 --> 04:50.170
Okay, fine.

04:50.170 --> 04:52.290
But put it on speaker so I can hear.
Okay.

04:52.290 --> 04:54.080
[ Ringing ]

04:54.080 --> 04:55.750
Zach: Hello?
Hey, Zach, it's Katie.

04:55.750 --> 04:57.250
Oh, hey, Katie.

04:57.250 --> 04:58.330
Courtney and I were just
talking about you guys.

04:58.330 --> 04:59.670
Us, too.

04:59.670 --> 05:02.460
We figured why not call
and make a plan to hang out.

05:02.460 --> 05:03.670
Courtney: How about dinner
tomorrow night?

05:03.670 --> 05:05.540
Oh, hey, Courtney!
Works for us.

05:05.540 --> 05:06.830
Zach: We found this great

05:06.830 --> 05:08.210
off-the-beaten-path
Vietnamese place.

05:08.210 --> 05:09.290
You guys like pho?

05:09.290 --> 05:11.250
[ High-pitched voice ]
Fo sho!

05:11.250 --> 05:12.170
Perfect.
See you guys tomorrow night.

05:12.170 --> 05:13.170
[ Cellphone beeps ]

05:13.170 --> 05:14.920
Who's the man?!
[ Normal voice ] I am!

05:14.920 --> 05:16.620
Who's the woman?!
That's not a saying!

05:16.620 --> 05:17.920
Feels sexist
leaving you out!

05:17.920 --> 05:19.580
We can't do this kind of crap
tomorrow night!

05:19.580 --> 05:23.170
♪♪

05:23.170 --> 05:24.790
Okay,
ground rules for tonight.

05:24.790 --> 05:26.000
Taylor's in charge,

05:26.000 --> 05:27.420
and there can be
no more disasters.

05:27.420 --> 05:29.120
What do you mean
by disasters?

05:29.120 --> 05:30.210
Last time
we let you babysit,

05:30.210 --> 05:31.290
you guys played hide-and-seek
with Anna-Kat

05:31.290 --> 05:32.380
and gave up
without telling her.

05:32.380 --> 05:33.750
She was zipped
inside an old suitcase

05:33.750 --> 05:35.080
for five hours.

05:35.080 --> 05:36.250
We didn't give up.

05:36.250 --> 05:37.380
We just never looked.

05:37.380 --> 05:39.380
This is your last shot.

05:39.380 --> 05:41.120
If you can't prove
that you're responsible,

05:41.120 --> 05:42.080
then you can't go to
the concert

05:42.080 --> 05:43.380
with your friends
next week.

05:43.380 --> 05:44.960
Got it?
Got it.

05:44.960 --> 05:47.120
This dinner we're going to
is important,

05:47.120 --> 05:49.330
so don't call unless
it's really an emergency.

05:49.330 --> 05:50.750
That means only call
from the hospital

05:50.750 --> 05:51.920
and not just
from the waiting room.

05:51.920 --> 05:53.380
Call once you're admitted

05:53.380 --> 05:54.710
and stretched out
on one of those wheely beds.

05:57.330 --> 05:58.580
Wait.
You guys can't leave.

05:58.580 --> 05:59.790
I want to tell you
what happened on my show,

05:59.790 --> 06:01.460
"Adventure Cats."

06:01.460 --> 06:02.670
Let's get out of here

06:02.670 --> 06:04.620
before she recounts
every minute in real time.

06:04.620 --> 06:07.880
So, Captain Meowington
was leading an expedition

06:07.880 --> 06:10.500
down the Amazon River
on a bamboo raft...

06:10.500 --> 06:12.380
That's so exciting!
Go, go, go, go, go!

06:12.380 --> 06:15.750
And then a snake just
fell down out of the trees,

06:15.750 --> 06:18.040
right onto
Captain Meowington's lap.

06:18.040 --> 06:21.080
Oh! The snake episode!

06:21.080 --> 06:24.120
Oliver was just asking
how it ends.

06:24.120 --> 06:25.330
Tell him.

06:25.330 --> 06:28.000
Don't waste another minute
on us.

06:30.500 --> 06:33.960
All right, let's clear our heads
of all of that.

06:33.960 --> 06:35.750
Shake it off.

06:35.750 --> 06:38.460
Remember,
we don't have kids.

06:38.460 --> 06:40.000
Did we leave them
enough money for pizza?

06:40.000 --> 06:42.000
I think so.
Wrong!

06:42.000 --> 06:43.880
The correct answer
is "Who?"

06:43.880 --> 06:45.080
because
we don't have kids.

06:45.080 --> 06:46.080
Be better!

06:46.080 --> 06:47.580
Noted.

06:47.580 --> 06:48.830
All right, let's do this. Greg!

06:48.830 --> 06:49.620
Your keychain.

06:49.620 --> 06:51.000
♪♪

06:51.000 --> 06:52.170
Oh, my God!

06:52.170 --> 06:53.960
[ Keys rattle ]

06:53.960 --> 06:54.830
[ Exhales sharply ]

06:54.830 --> 06:55.580
I'll get the spare.

06:55.580 --> 06:57.460
Okay.

06:57.460 --> 06:59.120
Anna-Kat:
Then Captain Meowington

06:59.120 --> 07:00.540
gave up
his rank and command

07:00.540 --> 07:02.460
to raise his kittens.

07:02.460 --> 07:04.040
Greg: Really?
I knew he had a heart of gold.

07:04.040 --> 07:04.880
Greg!

07:04.880 --> 07:07.120
Sorry about that.

07:07.120 --> 07:08.330
It just sounds like they're
taking a lot of risks

07:08.330 --> 07:09.380
in season two.

07:09.380 --> 07:10.380
Okay.

07:10.380 --> 07:15.080
♪♪

07:15.080 --> 07:17.000
Anna-Kat, dinner!

07:17.000 --> 07:18.620
There's a lot
riding on tonight.

07:18.620 --> 07:20.790
You and Anna-Kat
are my responsibility.

07:20.790 --> 07:23.210
Nothing can go wrong.
No one can get hurt.

07:23.210 --> 07:25.120
What's in it for me?
What do you mean?

07:25.120 --> 07:26.790
Well, you're getting
something out of this.

07:26.790 --> 07:28.000
I want something, too.
[ Sighs ]

07:28.000 --> 07:30.170
What's your price?
Okay.

07:30.170 --> 07:33.080
I want you to do
what Mom and Dad refuse to do --

07:33.080 --> 07:34.830
drive me past the biggest houses
in Westport,

07:34.830 --> 07:36.420
slowly...

07:36.420 --> 07:38.580
while I look up
their value on Zillow.

07:38.580 --> 07:40.210
No way.

07:40.210 --> 07:43.120
I will break my pinkie
right now.

07:43.120 --> 07:44.540
Okay, fine.

07:44.540 --> 07:45.750
It's a deal. Anna-Kat:
[ Clears throat ]

07:47.080 --> 07:48.670
Who's gonna wet my beak?

07:48.670 --> 07:49.880
What?

07:49.880 --> 07:51.000
Here's the thing.

07:51.000 --> 07:52.420
I need to write a story

07:52.420 --> 07:53.960
to read out loud
tomorrow night

07:53.960 --> 07:55.250
at the Kid Lit
assembly...

07:55.250 --> 07:57.460
only I don't feel like
writing it.

07:57.460 --> 07:58.710
Do you get
what I'm saying?

07:59.330 --> 08:00.420
No.

08:00.420 --> 08:02.880
She wants you
to write the story for her.

08:02.880 --> 08:04.790
And you're gonna help her
because she's kind of stupid.

08:04.790 --> 08:06.120
[ Scoffs ] Okay.

08:06.120 --> 08:07.420
What will happen
if we don't?

08:07.420 --> 08:09.750
I saved some baby teeth
just for this situation.

08:09.750 --> 08:11.540
[ Whimpers ] Ow!

08:11.540 --> 08:13.290
[ Fake crying ] Taylor let me
jump off the counter,

08:13.290 --> 08:15.330
and I knocked out
my tooth!

08:15.330 --> 08:16.460
[ Normal voice ]
Happy writing.

08:16.460 --> 08:19.210
♪♪

08:19.210 --> 08:20.540
[ Laughter ]

08:20.540 --> 08:21.500
Whoa.

08:21.500 --> 08:23.120
Mmm.

08:23.120 --> 08:25.080
We have been big fans of
Vietnamese food

08:25.080 --> 08:26.380
ever since
we went backpacking

08:26.380 --> 08:27.830
outside of Hanoi
last summer.

08:27.830 --> 08:30.000
Oh, yeah, we rappelled
down a waterfall,

08:30.000 --> 08:32.460
explored this tunnel system,
went sand-boarding...

08:32.460 --> 08:34.290
Wow.
But what about you?

08:34.290 --> 08:35.790
I bet you guys have taken
some great trips.

08:35.790 --> 08:37.790
Katie:
Oh, boy, have we.

08:37.790 --> 08:39.380
[ Both laugh nervously ]

08:39.380 --> 08:41.080
Which one do you want
to talk about first?

08:41.080 --> 08:42.330
Let's just
pick a favorite.

08:42.330 --> 08:44.790
Which one is our favorite, Greg?
Um...

08:44.790 --> 08:46.250
Katie:
When was our last vacation?

08:46.250 --> 08:48.000
Does staying
at the Motel Six for a weekend

08:48.000 --> 08:49.580
after our pipes burst count?

08:49.580 --> 08:54.620
I think our favorite trip
probably was...

08:54.620 --> 08:56.040
when we went rafting
down the Amazon.

08:56.040 --> 08:57.000
Right, honey?

08:57.000 --> 08:58.250
Oh.
Whoa.

08:58.250 --> 09:00.250
We were
some adventurous cats,

09:00.250 --> 09:02.040
weren't we, Katie?

09:02.040 --> 09:04.420
That's right.

09:04.420 --> 09:06.920
We were on bamboo rafts.

09:06.920 --> 09:09.380
Yeah, our captain Me-Ow
warned us

09:09.380 --> 09:11.710
that it wasn't a trip.

09:11.710 --> 09:13.120
It was an exercise
in survival.

09:13.120 --> 09:14.710
We were
admiring the scenery,

09:14.710 --> 09:17.330
when this giant snake
dropped down from the trees.

09:17.330 --> 09:18.620
Whoa.
So what'd you guys do?

09:18.620 --> 09:21.620
[ Laughs ]
What did we do?

09:21.620 --> 09:23.460
My instincts
just kicked in,

09:23.460 --> 09:24.670
and I punched it
in the face.

09:24.670 --> 09:26.210
Knocked it out cold.

09:26.210 --> 09:27.210
Our Captain Me-Ow...

09:27.210 --> 09:28.710
Who turned out to be
a real sweetheart...

09:28.710 --> 09:29.750
...skinned it,
cooked it up.

09:29.750 --> 09:31.120
Best dinner we ever had.

09:31.120 --> 09:33.790
Whoa.
I'm so jealous.

09:33.790 --> 09:35.420
Somebody
is allergic to snake.

09:35.420 --> 09:40.250
[ Laughter ]

09:40.250 --> 09:42.120
So, we heard about
this place in town

09:42.120 --> 09:43.620
that serves
bespoke cocktails.

09:43.620 --> 09:44.920
Just pick a night
and we're there.

09:44.920 --> 09:46.080
The night is now!

09:46.080 --> 09:47.170
We'll get the coats.

09:48.830 --> 09:50.330
Are they serious?
It's almost 9:30.

09:50.330 --> 09:52.580
We're already pushing our bedtime.
I know.

09:52.580 --> 09:54.500
We should be in bed with me
putting stuff in my Amazon cart

09:54.500 --> 09:56.080
and you telling me
not to push the buy button.

09:56.080 --> 09:57.670
If we go to this bar,
we still have to wake up early

09:57.670 --> 09:58.830
and deal with the kids,

09:58.830 --> 10:00.120
and I have to help
Anna-Kat with her story.

10:00.120 --> 10:01.250
If we don't
go to this bar,

10:01.250 --> 10:02.750
they could meet
a real kid-less couple

10:02.750 --> 10:04.330
who knows what the hell
bespoke cocktails actually are.

10:04.330 --> 10:05.750
We could lose them,
Greg.

10:05.750 --> 10:07.080
Come on.

10:07.080 --> 10:08.920
We never
put ourselves first.

10:08.920 --> 10:10.620
Let's do something for us
for a change.

10:10.620 --> 10:12.500
All right, let's do it.

10:12.500 --> 10:14.330
Look out, 11:00,
here come the Ottos!

10:14.330 --> 10:15.250
[ Laughs ]

10:15.250 --> 10:16.920
♪♪

10:21.710 --> 10:23.920
Last night was fun.
The Ottos saw midnight.

10:23.920 --> 10:26.380
Then I took a brief micro nap
in the ladies room to rally,

10:26.380 --> 10:27.920
and then we saw 12:45.

10:27.920 --> 10:28.830
Do you think
that they liked us?

10:28.830 --> 10:30.250
I hope so.

10:30.250 --> 10:31.330
What happens now?
Do we call them?

10:31.330 --> 10:32.620
I don't know
how this works.

10:32.620 --> 10:34.000
[ Cellphone chimes ]
[ Gasps ]

10:35.790 --> 10:36.790
It's not me! It's you!

10:36.790 --> 10:38.080
Help me find my phone!

10:40.580 --> 10:41.580
Call it!

10:41.580 --> 10:43.120
Wait. It's in my hand.

10:43.120 --> 10:44.540
It's a text from Zach!
[ Gasps ]

10:44.540 --> 10:46.080
They don't play games!
They had fun!

10:46.080 --> 10:47.710
What did they say exactly?
"We had fun!"

10:47.710 --> 10:49.210
Yes!

10:49.210 --> 10:51.420
Anna-Kat: Mama,
where's my clean underwear?

10:51.420 --> 10:53.290
Never mind.
Going inside-out.

10:53.290 --> 10:54.170
Ugh, back to reality.

10:54.170 --> 10:55.460
I got to go make breakfast,

10:55.460 --> 10:57.420
and you need to help Anna-Kat
with her story.

10:57.420 --> 10:58.620
I'm texting him back.
What do you think of this?

10:58.620 --> 10:59.830
"We had fun, too.

10:59.830 --> 11:01.120
Love you guys.

11:01.120 --> 11:02.500
Regards, Greg"?

11:02.500 --> 11:04.790
That is terrible,
but reassuring.

11:04.790 --> 11:06.040
You have no future
in online dating.

11:06.040 --> 11:07.290
You're stuck with me
forever.

11:07.290 --> 11:08.500
[ Chuckles ]

11:08.500 --> 11:14.460
♪♪

11:14.460 --> 11:16.580
So, how did it go
last night?

11:16.580 --> 11:18.000
Perfect.

11:18.000 --> 11:19.960
You know I'd love to throw
this one under the bus,

11:19.960 --> 11:21.580
but she did great.

11:21.580 --> 11:22.960
Anna-Kat:
It's true, Mama.

11:22.960 --> 11:24.920
They spent the whole time
helping me with my story

11:24.920 --> 11:26.580
for the Kid Lit assembly
tonight.

11:26.580 --> 11:27.920
I thought I was gonna
help you with that.

11:27.920 --> 11:29.960
Guess you don't
need to anymore.

11:29.960 --> 11:31.540
Are you seeing this?

11:31.540 --> 11:33.880
Yeah, we stepped back,
and they're fine without us.

11:33.880 --> 11:35.500
What are we gonna do with
all our newfound free time?

11:38.580 --> 11:40.540
But we're already dressed
for the day --

11:40.540 --> 11:41.920
What am I saying?
Who cares?

11:41.920 --> 11:45.290
[ Jazz music plays ]

11:45.290 --> 11:47.420
Story time.
Let me hear what you got.

11:47.420 --> 11:49.040
Okay, so we have
a couple of options

11:49.040 --> 11:50.210
for you to choose from.

11:50.210 --> 11:52.580
The first is a story
about friendship,

11:52.580 --> 11:54.250
and it starts
with two brown bears --

11:54.250 --> 11:55.330
Pass.
What's next?

11:55.330 --> 11:57.880
Well, we have another one
about a mouse

11:57.880 --> 11:59.620
who's trying to track down
a missing skateboard.

11:59.620 --> 12:01.210
No, too cute.

12:01.210 --> 12:02.460
But you watch
"Adventure Cats,"

12:02.460 --> 12:03.670
and that's
all about kittens.

12:03.670 --> 12:05.580
I just watch that
to unwind.

12:05.580 --> 12:08.000
Here are a few things
I want in my story --

12:08.000 --> 12:11.330
The Donner Party,
flesh-eating super-viruses,

12:11.330 --> 12:12.750
and dandelions.

12:12.750 --> 12:14.330
What do those even
have to do with each other?

12:14.330 --> 12:16.290
Seems like
a writer problem.

12:16.290 --> 12:17.670
Make it work.

12:17.670 --> 12:24.580
♪♪

12:24.580 --> 12:26.830
And Zach and Courtney took us
to this cool restaurant,

12:26.830 --> 12:28.540
then to a secret bar,
and get this --

12:28.540 --> 12:31.920
this morning,
Greg and I even had sex.

12:31.920 --> 12:33.250
[ Gasps ]
Morning sex?

12:33.250 --> 12:35.250
Okay, quick question.

12:35.250 --> 12:36.420
Was the bed already made,

12:36.420 --> 12:38.420
and if so,
did you then remake it?

12:38.420 --> 12:40.580
I'm telling you,
hanging out with this couple

12:40.580 --> 12:42.250
reminded us
that we once had a life

12:42.250 --> 12:43.250
outside of our kids.

12:43.250 --> 12:44.670
Well,
enjoy it while you can.

12:44.670 --> 12:46.040
Take it
from a single mom --

12:46.040 --> 12:47.380
you can only
hide your kids

12:47.380 --> 12:49.120
from the people you're dating
for so long.

12:49.120 --> 12:51.250
'Cause when they find out,
they'll dump you.

12:51.250 --> 12:52.750
Because you're not
spontaneous.

12:52.750 --> 12:54.080
And you can't
go to Nantucket

12:54.080 --> 12:55.960
because you got a kid
that didn't listen to you

12:55.960 --> 12:58.000
and went outside without
a jacket and got sick,

12:58.000 --> 12:59.920
so now you're staying home
while she's at a beachhouse

12:59.920 --> 13:02.120
with some bitch
named Ruth.

13:02.120 --> 13:04.170
Don't worry.
We have a plan.

13:04.170 --> 13:05.670
We're gonna
get them invested

13:05.670 --> 13:07.000
in a fake version
of ourselves,

13:07.000 --> 13:08.540
then,
when they fall in love,

13:08.540 --> 13:10.380
we're gonna reveal
our three little flaws.

13:10.380 --> 13:12.420
Oh! I did the same thing
with Richard.

13:12.420 --> 13:14.250
I let him believe
I was nice.

13:14.250 --> 13:16.000
There's no way
some bitch named "Ruth"

13:16.000 --> 13:17.080
is hotter than I am.

13:17.080 --> 13:18.290
Not possible.

13:18.290 --> 13:27.000
♪♪

13:27.000 --> 13:28.210
The kids are really
getting along.

13:28.210 --> 13:29.790
Don't talk about it.
You'll jinx it.

13:29.790 --> 13:31.380
You said our kids
had great taste in music,

13:31.380 --> 13:33.170
then it was "Call Me Maybe"
for a whole year.

13:33.170 --> 13:34.500
Let's take advantage
of this

13:34.500 --> 13:36.620
and have Taylor watch the kids
again tonight.

13:36.620 --> 13:38.290
We can't. We have Anna-Kat's
Lit assembly at 6:00.

13:38.290 --> 13:40.710
Aw, man.
I forgot about that.

13:40.710 --> 13:43.210
Anna-Kat, how many kids
are reading tonight?

13:43.210 --> 13:45.290
There are
24 kids in my class,

13:45.290 --> 13:47.540
but there are two classes,
so 48.

13:47.540 --> 13:49.500
[ Sighs ] So fun!

13:50.920 --> 13:52.120
If I take off running
right now,

13:52.120 --> 13:53.540
I can get home, pack,

13:53.540 --> 13:54.960
and be in Canada
by tomorrow morning.

13:54.960 --> 13:56.420
You are not going to Canada.

13:56.420 --> 13:57.920
Get out of my head, man.

13:57.920 --> 14:00.250
I'm really excited
for you to hear my story.

14:00.250 --> 14:01.540
It's pretty amazing.

14:01.540 --> 14:03.120
It better be amazing,

14:03.120 --> 14:05.500
or I'll lock myself
in my toy chest

14:05.500 --> 14:07.580
and say that you kept me there
all night.

14:07.580 --> 14:09.120
You wouldn't.

14:09.120 --> 14:10.420
Oh, yeah?

14:10.420 --> 14:12.710
"It's so dark in here.

14:12.710 --> 14:14.210
I can't...breathe!"

14:14.210 --> 14:16.620
[ Breathing heavily ]

14:16.620 --> 14:18.580
Now give me a taste
of your ice cream.

14:19.210 --> 14:20.750
Aww, they're sharing.

14:20.750 --> 14:22.040
We're Parents of the Year.

14:22.040 --> 14:23.670
[ Chuckles ] Oh, crap, Greg!
Look!

14:24.580 --> 14:26.210
We can't be seen
with these jokers.

14:26.210 --> 14:27.460
Guys, who wants candy?

14:27.460 --> 14:28.710
You always say

14:28.710 --> 14:30.830
we're not allowed to have
two sweets in one day.

14:30.830 --> 14:32.750
Young lady, when your father
tells you to eat candy,

14:32.750 --> 14:33.540
you eat candy.

14:34.120 --> 14:35.290
Come on, come on!

14:39.170 --> 14:40.330
Anna-Kat's sweater!

14:41.290 --> 14:43.170
Oh, I think
you dropped this.

14:43.170 --> 14:45.080
You dropped it.

14:45.080 --> 14:47.080
[ Gasps ] Hey, look!
Hey!

14:47.080 --> 14:48.380
It's our new best friends!
Greg: [ Laughs ]

14:48.380 --> 14:50.000
Hey, guys!

14:50.000 --> 14:51.380
Just taking
a leisurely stroll.

14:51.380 --> 14:53.330
Just the two of us,
which we do every day.

14:53.330 --> 14:55.330
'Cause we have the time.

14:55.330 --> 14:56.500
[ Laughs ]

14:56.500 --> 14:57.790
We were just about
to call you guys.

14:57.790 --> 14:59.040
Zach: Oh, yeah!

14:59.040 --> 15:00.080
Yeah,
we decided to head up

15:00.080 --> 15:01.380
to our ski house
in New Hampshire.

15:01.380 --> 15:02.790
Hit the hot tub,
snowmobile in the morning,

15:02.790 --> 15:03.880
and then head back
tomorrow.

15:03.880 --> 15:05.080
Classic H-T-Sno-mo.

15:05.080 --> 15:06.290
Sounds amazing!

15:06.290 --> 15:07.540
We'd love for you guys
to come

15:07.540 --> 15:08.960
if you don't already
have plans tonight.

15:08.960 --> 15:10.500
Did we have something
we were supposed to do?

15:10.500 --> 15:11.880
Something about an up-and-coming
authors symposium?

15:11.880 --> 15:13.500
Oh, yeah.

15:13.500 --> 15:15.040
Oh, shoot.
Well, I guess we could ask --

15:15.040 --> 15:16.540
No, no, no!
We're in!

15:16.540 --> 15:17.830
Oh. Okay, great. Hey, I'll
text you the address.

15:17.830 --> 15:18.790
Greg: Great.
All right.

15:19.750 --> 15:21.330
An overnighter.

15:21.330 --> 15:23.330
This is the way
relationships are cemented.

15:23.330 --> 15:24.920
Would it be lame if I wore
a T-shirt in the hot tub?

15:24.920 --> 15:25.880
Yeah.

15:25.880 --> 15:27.120
[ Doorbell jingles ]

15:27.120 --> 15:29.710
Anna-Kat:
Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaah!

15:29.710 --> 15:31.500
I think she's probably
had enough sugar.

15:35.380 --> 15:37.290
♪♪

15:37.290 --> 15:38.960
I know it's just
a kid-free night

15:38.960 --> 15:40.250
with new friends
in a new place,

15:40.250 --> 15:41.750
but I'm super-excited.
Greg: Me too.

15:41.750 --> 15:44.210
Are these good lounge-around-
the-ski-lodge pants,

15:44.210 --> 15:45.460
or do they look
too much like pajamas?

15:45.460 --> 15:46.830
They're good.
But wear underwear.

15:46.830 --> 15:47.920
Reduce floppage.

15:47.920 --> 15:48.920
Yes.

15:48.920 --> 15:50.330
I refuse to feel guilty

15:50.330 --> 15:51.500
for missing
Anna-Kat's reading tonight.

15:51.500 --> 15:53.920
We have a responsibility
to ourselves,

15:53.920 --> 15:55.380
to our relationship,

15:55.380 --> 15:58.250
to the Gods of Spontaneous
Marital Morning Sex.

15:58.250 --> 16:00.620
I love those guys.
I love you guys!

16:00.620 --> 16:02.120
Half of the parents
in this town

16:02.120 --> 16:03.290
spend zero time
with their kids.

16:03.290 --> 16:04.670
Then they put on
this big show

16:04.670 --> 16:06.250
by going to
every last school event,

16:06.250 --> 16:07.500
like that makes them
good parents.

16:07.500 --> 16:08.460
That's what they do.

16:08.460 --> 16:09.960
That's totally
what they do.

16:09.960 --> 16:11.880
They're like, "Ooh!
I'm such a good mother!

16:11.880 --> 16:14.170
The nanny feeds them,
the maid cleans up after them,

16:14.170 --> 16:16.000
but I'm here at the stupid
Kid Lit Festival."

16:16.000 --> 16:17.670
"Ooh,
I'm an awesome dad,

16:17.670 --> 16:19.250
I play 72 holes of golf
a week

16:19.250 --> 16:21.420
and read texts when my kids
are trying to talk to me,

16:21.420 --> 16:22.710
but look at me now!

16:22.710 --> 16:23.750
I'm in the front row,

16:23.750 --> 16:25.170
taping the whole thing
on my phone

16:25.170 --> 16:27.040
like I'm not
a total douche."

16:27.040 --> 16:29.000
And that's
not parenting.

16:29.000 --> 16:30.380
It most certainly
is not.

16:30.380 --> 16:32.960
Parenting is the daily grind
of caring for kids

16:32.960 --> 16:34.120
while doing
the painstaking work

16:34.120 --> 16:34.880
of shaping
their character.

16:34.880 --> 16:36.380
That's what we do.

16:36.380 --> 16:37.880
That's all we do, Greg.

16:37.880 --> 16:39.420
That is our entire life.

16:39.420 --> 16:41.250
In fact, one could argue
that by skipping this event,

16:41.250 --> 16:42.710
we're teaching Anna-Kat
a lesson in independence.

16:42.710 --> 16:44.330
Yes.

16:44.330 --> 16:46.250
By going away, we're actually
being there for her more

16:46.250 --> 16:46.960
than if we stayed.

16:46.960 --> 16:48.580
I buy that.

16:48.580 --> 16:50.080
So, for real, what happens
when Anna-Kat's onstage

16:50.080 --> 16:51.580
and looks out in the audience
and we're not there?

16:51.580 --> 16:52.670
She'll be fine.

16:52.670 --> 16:53.960
We'll buy her ice cream
with extra toppings,

16:53.960 --> 16:54.830
and she'll get over it.

16:54.830 --> 16:56.170
So you're saying

16:56.170 --> 16:57.920
for the price of a couple
of crumbled-up Oreos,

16:57.920 --> 16:58.920
we can reclaim our lives?

16:58.920 --> 16:59.920
I'm in!

16:59.920 --> 17:00.830
[ Chuckles ]

17:00.830 --> 17:02.460
♪♪

17:02.460 --> 17:03.880
We good to go?

17:03.880 --> 17:05.540
Yeah.
Everything's packed.

17:05.540 --> 17:07.250
Angela's gonna take the kids
to the Lit assembly

17:07.250 --> 17:08.620
and stay the night.

17:08.620 --> 17:10.210
And I told the kids
that their great aunt passed,

17:10.210 --> 17:11.460
and we had to go
to the funeral.

17:11.460 --> 17:13.580
How many great aunts
is that now?

17:13.580 --> 17:15.460
I think I'm up to seven,
and they still haven't noticed.

17:15.460 --> 17:16.420
[ Laughs ]

17:17.580 --> 17:18.620
We're on our way,

17:18.620 --> 17:19.920
and we don't feel guilty
at all, do we?

17:19.920 --> 17:21.210
Now floor it!

17:21.210 --> 17:24.080
♪♪

17:24.080 --> 17:26.040
We're having
such an amazing time!

17:26.040 --> 17:27.710
Wish you were here!
Cheers!

17:27.710 --> 17:29.250
Whoo!

17:29.250 --> 17:30.620
[ Sighs ]
[ Sighs ]

17:30.620 --> 17:31.710
Remember driveway us?

17:31.710 --> 17:33.290
They had it all
figured out.

17:33.290 --> 17:34.620
Highway us,

17:34.620 --> 17:36.540
that's where it all
started to crumble.

17:36.540 --> 17:39.830
...And so, the two rabbits
sat down at the table

17:39.830 --> 17:40.880
and shared the carrot.

17:40.880 --> 17:42.250
The end.

17:42.250 --> 17:44.210
[ Applause ]

17:44.210 --> 17:45.620
Well, that was awful.

17:45.620 --> 17:47.380
Still,
we did the right thing.

17:47.380 --> 17:48.380
♪♪

17:48.380 --> 17:50.000
Although the zebra
had stripes

17:50.000 --> 17:52.040
and the leopard had spots,

17:52.040 --> 17:53.830
they decided
they could still be friends.

17:53.830 --> 17:55.040
The end.

17:55.040 --> 17:59.250
[ Applause ]

17:59.250 --> 18:01.000
Still think we did
the right thing?

18:01.000 --> 18:04.420
Uhhhhh...

18:04.420 --> 18:06.330
The sun told the cloud
to stop crying.

18:06.330 --> 18:07.380
It did.

18:07.380 --> 18:08.790
Then all
the children of the world

18:08.790 --> 18:09.960
came out to play.

18:09.960 --> 18:11.080
The end.

18:11.080 --> 18:15.670
[ Applause ]

18:15.670 --> 18:17.120
Principal Ablin:
Everyone having a good time?

18:18.620 --> 18:20.380
I sure am.

18:20.380 --> 18:22.500
Please welcome
Anna-Kat Otto.

18:22.500 --> 18:24.210
Oh.

18:24.210 --> 18:30.830
[ Applause ]

18:30.830 --> 18:32.210
Once upon a time,

18:32.210 --> 18:34.000
when America
was a young nation,

18:34.000 --> 18:35.710
a family of pioneers

18:35.710 --> 18:37.960
decided to take a risk
and head West,

18:37.960 --> 18:40.250
into the new frontier...

18:40.250 --> 18:42.500
You are so going to that
concert with your friends.

18:42.500 --> 18:44.670
♪♪

18:44.670 --> 18:46.670
Once the flesh-eating bacteria
took over the camp,

18:46.670 --> 18:48.210
no one was safe.

18:48.210 --> 18:50.500
Those who died
were actually the lucky ones.

18:50.500 --> 18:51.710
Those who didn't
were so hungry

18:51.710 --> 18:53.170
they had no choice

18:53.170 --> 18:54.580
but to eat
their family members...

18:55.540 --> 18:57.000
...and not
even dandelions

18:57.000 --> 18:58.040
would grow
over their graves.

19:01.790 --> 19:03.620
[ Man coughs ]

19:03.620 --> 19:05.040
The end.

19:05.040 --> 19:08.880
[ Both clapping ]

19:08.880 --> 19:12.960
You're so not going to that
concert with your friends.

19:12.960 --> 19:15.790
♪♪

19:15.790 --> 19:17.380
Are you kidding me
with that story?

19:17.380 --> 19:18.790
What were you two
thinking?

19:18.790 --> 19:20.000
We tried
to pitch her bunnies.

19:20.000 --> 19:21.250
Yeah,
but then she got mad

19:21.250 --> 19:22.460
and made us
work through dinner.

19:22.460 --> 19:24.290
Am I the only one
who thought it went well?

19:26.880 --> 19:28.250
As much as
I want to blame them,

19:28.250 --> 19:29.460
which I really, really
want to do,

19:29.460 --> 19:31.000
the truth is,

19:31.000 --> 19:32.500
this is on us.
I know.

19:32.500 --> 19:34.040
We were so caught up enjoying
our kid-less life

19:34.040 --> 19:35.120
with our kid-less friends,

19:35.120 --> 19:36.040
we took our eyes
off the ball.

19:36.040 --> 19:37.580
I'm glad
we came to our senses.

19:37.580 --> 19:39.420
Did you see
Anna-Kat's face

19:39.420 --> 19:40.330
when she looked out
in the audience

19:40.330 --> 19:41.330
and saw we were there?

19:41.330 --> 19:42.580
Yeah.

19:42.580 --> 19:44.540
Maybe Highway Us knew
what they were doing.

19:44.540 --> 19:46.460
75% of parenting is doing stuff
you don't want to do.

19:46.460 --> 19:47.960
I think
it's closer to 90%.

19:47.960 --> 19:50.120
Good news is,
once they're out of the house,

19:50.120 --> 19:51.790
and it's just
the two of us again,

19:51.790 --> 19:53.120
we know
we've still got it.

19:53.120 --> 19:54.710
Damn right we do.

19:56.210 --> 19:58.620
You guys can still have it,
just hide it.

20:00.710 --> 20:01.830
95%.

20:01.830 --> 20:02.830
Maybe higher.

20:02.830 --> 20:04.710
♪♪

20:08.580 --> 20:13.380
♪♪

20:13.380 --> 20:15.250
So we're just going
to come right out

20:15.250 --> 20:16.750
and tell them the truth --

20:16.750 --> 20:17.750
we have kids.
Yep.

20:17.750 --> 20:19.040
And if they want
to break up with us,

20:19.040 --> 20:20.170
we're not gonna beg.
[ Door opens ]

20:20.170 --> 20:22.790
-Hey!
-Hi!

20:22.790 --> 20:24.790
Listen, we're so sorry

20:24.790 --> 20:26.380
that we had to cancel with you
last-minute.

20:26.380 --> 20:28.170
We have something
we wanted to tell you,

20:28.170 --> 20:29.620
but we wanted to do it
in person.

20:29.620 --> 20:30.790
